    "The formal definitions of the two initializations are written as:w d k = softmax( N i=1 (t j i,k) K k=1 N i=1 (t j i,k)) w s p,k = softmax( i∈Sp (t j i,k) K k=1 i∈Sp (t j i,k))(11)where w d k, w s p,k are initialized weights averaged on all data and each sample respectively, softmax(•) denotes the softmax function applied along the label dimension, and S p is the extracted patch set of p-th sample.",
    "Rather than weights at the label-level, weights at the instance-level, namely a scalar weight for each instance instead of a vector weight, are also evaluated in the ablation study.",
